  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "16. Rather, \"With fire will Jehovah judge, and with His sword (He will judge) all flesh.\" The parallelism and collocation of the Hebrew words favor this (Isa 65:12).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "all flesh—that is, all who are the objects of His wrath. The godly shall be hidden by the Lord in a place of safety away from the scene of judgment (Isa 26:20, 21; Ps 31:20; 1Th 4:16, 17).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
